<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="6Aug1921"><font color="red">6 August 1921</font>, <cite>Letters I</cite> (JJ to Frank Budgen): Received first instalment of <cite>Gibraltar</cite>. What is wrong with the rest? &hellip; I send you 1st part of <cite>Penelope</cite> in its draft form to let you see it and have your opinion. This is only the <i>draft</i> a great deal will be added or changed on 3 proofs. Let me know how it strikes you and return it by registered post as quickly as possible. Will send you more money on Monday or Tuesday for the following if obtainable: (1) Love&apos;s Old Sweet Song. (2) In Old Madrid. (3) Fanny Hill <cite>Memoirs</cite> (unexpurgated). If you find this latter you can put a stop on it &hellip; To understand <cite>Penelope</cite> well you should have an idea of <cite>Ithaca</cite> but it is not ready</div>
